To compute the LIX readability score, we need to analyze the text and count the following parameters:

1. Number of words (n)
2. Number of sentences (m)
3. Number of long words (more than 6 letters) (l)

Analyzing the text, we get:

n (number of words) = 47
m (number of sentences) = 4
l (number of long words) = 13 (here are the long words: människa, speciell, dokumentär, högerns, vinklad)

The LIX formula is: 

LIX = ((l / n) * 100) + ((n / m) * 0.4)

Computing the values:

(l / n) = 13 / 47 ≈ 0.277
(l / n) * 100 ≈ 0.277 * 100 ≈ 27.7
(n / m) = 47 / 4 ≈ 11.75
(n / m) * 0.4 ≈ 11.75 * 0.4 ≈ 4.7
LIX ≈ 27.7 + 4.7 ≈ 32.4

Rounding the score to the nearest integer:
LIX = 32